HEADWORD: Fouquieria
<hw>Fouquieria</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a genus of resinous succulent
trees or shrubs of desert and semi-desert regions of the southwestern U.
S. that are leafless most of the year.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Fouquieria</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
